   The following portions of rdprrap are derived from, ported from, or
   closely mirror behavior of stascorp/rdpwrap:

     - crates/rdprrap-check/src/disc_reason.rs
         Disconnect-reason code → text table. Structurally ported from
         the `case DiscReason of` block in rdpwrap's RDPCheck source.
         (The displayed strings themselves are from Microsoft's public
         MSTSCAX ExtendedDisconnectReasonCode documentation and are
         included under that public documentation grant, not under
         Apache-2.0.)

     - crates/rdprrap-check/src/main.rs
         rdprrap-check is a Rust rewrite of rdpwrap's RDPCheck.exe.

     - crates/rdprrap-check/src/rdp.rs
         Loopback address `127.0.0.2` reuse follows rdpwrap's choice.

     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/version.rs
         Version-gate preflight mirrors rdpwrap's supported-version set.

     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/service.rs
         netsvcs cohort-service restart mirrors rdpwrap's RDPWInst logic
         (adapted to `EnumServicesStatusExW`).

     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/install.rs
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/firewall.rs
     - crates/rdprrap-installer/src/contract.rs
         Install directory, ACL hardening target set, firewall-rule
         behavior, and HKLM layout all match rdpwrap's RDPWInst.dpr
         contract for drop-in compatibility.

     - crates/rdprrap-conf/src/diag.rs (`WrapperState::InstalledRdpWrap`
         detection)
         Recognizes an existing rdpwrap.dll ServiceDll deployment for
         display purposes.

